<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62c843ca-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s4029"><num value="4029">§ 4029.</num><heading> Regulations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id62c843cb-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s4029/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Not later than 12 months after <date date="1994-10-25">October 25, 1994</date>, the Secretary shall promulgate final regulations for the implementation of this subchapter. All regulations promulgated pursuant to this subchapter shall be developed by the Secretary with the full and active participation of the Indian tribes with trust funds held by the Secretary and other affected Indian tribes.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id62c843cc-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s4029/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Effect</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The lack of promulgated regulations shall not limit the effect of this subchapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id62c843cd-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/412/tII/s209">Pub. L. 103–412, title II, § 209</ref>, <date date="1994-10-25">Oct. 25, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/4243">108 Stat. 4243</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
